Delta Sugar of Egypt to Buy Land Plot for New Plant, Mal Reports

-- B y   A h m e d   A   N a m a t a l l a
-- 
2011-04-13T07:55:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-13/delta-sugar-of-egypt-to-buy-land-plot-for-new-plant-mal-reports.html
Delta Sugar has agreed to buy a 300
feddan (311 acre) plot of land from Egypt’s Ministry of
Endowments for 53 million Egyptian pounds ($8.9 million),  Al Mal 
reported, citing Masoud Hamed, Delta’s director of
administrative affairs.  The company plans to build a new plant that will have the
capacity to produce 125,000 tons of sugar, 90,000 tons of
molasses and 90,000 tons of  animal feed , the Cairo-based
business daily said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Cairo at 
 anamatalla@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  